rows.text: He became head of government again from July 1958 to January 1959, when his steamroller tactics lost him the support of his own Christian Democratic colleagues. He learned from the experience, and became wiser in the ways of cooperating and compromising. He had been a leading proponent of such an "opening to the centre-left" for years.
